Title: The Long Way Home
Credit: written by
Author: A. N. Author
Draft date: 2026-07-17
Contact: hello@example.com

INT. NIGHT TRAIN - SLEEPER CAR - NIGHT

Rain streaks the window. MAI, 30s, watches the dark countryside blur past. Across from her, an OLD CONDUCTOR punches tickets with mechanical patience.

OLD CONDUCTOR
Last stop's not for hours yet.

MAI
(not looking up)
I know. I've done this trip before.

The conductor pauses, studies her.

OLD CONDUCTOR
Nobody rides this line twice for the scenery.

MAI
Nobody rides it once for the scenery.

MAI
It never is.

OLD CONDUCTOR ^
It never is.

They share a small, tired smile.

CUT TO:

EXT. RIVERSIDE PLATFORM - DAWN

Grey light. Mist off the water. Mai steps down onto the empty platform, suitcase in hand.

MAI (V.O.)
Home was never a place. It was the going.

.A TITLE CARD FADES UP

> THE LONG WAY HOME <

FADE OUT.
